    feat(conference)(conference-detail): collapse all three forks onto ConferenceDetail; audit home render

    Point the /2024, /2025, /2026 loaders at the shared ConferenceDetail
    module (Branch 3.3) and delete the ~600 lines of forked JSX in each fork
    (subtract-before-you-add: the duplicated detail page dies once, the three
    loaders shrink to thin getConference->pass-through entries).

    Home-route conference rendering audit (plan's codex->claude CONCERN): the
    home _index.tsx renders the Current Conference as a distinct evergreen hero
    teaser (themed background, dates/location/tagline/countdown, no
    register/schedule CTAs) and does NOT duplicate any ConferenceDetail
    section (MapSection/SpeakersAndSeminars/RegistrationSection/FaqSection).
    It is not a fourth fork; per the plan it is noted and left as-is. No
    fourth divergence point survives this branch.

    Meta titles now use the route's literal year instead of
    new Date().getFullYear() (a latent bug that rendered the current year on
    every /YYYY route), keeping each route's title/description self-consistent.

